<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="580" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1575,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1575,1600]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The genus can be recognized by the following combination of features: (I) segment X with a pair of long ventrolateral process extending into genital capsule; (II) each pygofer side with a ventral lanceolate process originating near midlength and extended outside the pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[858,928,1647,1672]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,199,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1855]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 14. Male holotype and female paratype genitalia of D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 7. Pygofer and segment X, lateral view; 8. Pygofer and segment X, dorsal view; 9. Style, dorsal view; 10. Connective, dorsal view; 11. Female sternite VII, ventral view; 12. Aedeagus, lateral view; 13. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 14. Subgenital plates and valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168337/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); (III) head broad and rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1299,1378,1647,1672]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[199,1390,411,1935]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1392,411,1943]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Head of male holotype of Duocrassana longula gen. and sp. nov. 1. Dorsal view; 2. Frontal view; 3. Lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168335/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 18. D" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[306,1315,266,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 18. D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 15. Male, dorsal view; 16. Female, dorsal habitus; 17 a. Female, face details (in INHS); 17 b. Female, face details (in CZUG); 18. Female, lateral habitus. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268273/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">15– 17</figureCitation>
); (IV) wings well developed, simple venation, without marks or bands (
<figureCitation box="[1012,1094,1684,1709]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 6. D" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[159,1436,231,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,227,1817]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 6. D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 4. Forewing, dorsal view; 5 a. Front femur, frontal view; 5 b. Front tibia, frontal view; 6 a. Hind tibia, dorsal view; 6 b. Hind tarsomeres, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168336/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1108,1228,1684,1709]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 18. D" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[306,1315,266,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 18. D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 15. Male, dorsal view; 16. Female, dorsal habitus; 17 a. Female, face details (in INHS); 17 b. Female, face details (in CZUG); 18. Female, lateral habitus. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268273/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">15, 16, 18</figureCitation>
); (V) gonoduct of aedeagus sclerotized anterior to the aedeagal base (
<figureCitation box="[724,808,1719,1744]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,199,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1855]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 14. Male holotype and female paratype genitalia of D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 7. Pygofer and segment X, lateral view; 8. Pygofer and segment X, dorsal view; 9. Style, dorsal view; 10. Connective, dorsal view; 11. Female sternite VII, ventral view; 12. Aedeagus, lateral view; 13. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 14. Subgenital plates and valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168337/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
); (VI) aedeagus bilobed at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1181,1264,1719,1744]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,199,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1855]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 14. Male holotype and female paratype genitalia of D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 7. Pygofer and segment X, lateral view; 8. Pygofer and segment X, dorsal view; 9. Style, dorsal view; 10. Connective, dorsal view; 11. Female sternite VII, ventral view; 12. Aedeagus, lateral view; 13. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 14. Subgenital plates and valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168337/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
); (VII) without spots or bands at the pronotum and scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[674,781,1756,1781]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[199,1390,411,1935]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1392,411,1943]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Head of male holotype of Duocrassana longula gen. and sp. nov. 1. Dorsal view; 2. Frontal view; 3. Lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168335/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Figs. 1, 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[793,867,1756,1781]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 18. D" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[306,1315,266,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 18. D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 15. Male, dorsal view; 16. Female, dorsal habitus; 17 a. Female, face details (in INHS); 17 b. Female, face details (in CZUG); 18. Female, lateral habitus. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268273/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">15–18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="586" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1575,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1791,1816]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Description</emphasis>
. Body somewhat robust, overall dorsal coloration light brown with obscure paler and darker markings on head, pronotum, scutellum and wings (
<figureCitation box="[733,817,1828,1853]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 18. D" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[306,1315,266,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 18. D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 15. Male, dorsal view; 16. Female, dorsal habitus; 17 a. Female, face details (in INHS); 17 b. Female, face details (in CZUG); 18. Female, lateral habitus. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268273/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Venter of head, thorax and abdomen with dark brown markings. Male weakly marked in crown with a fuscous band, female marked same, but more intense than male (
<figureCitation box="[159,297,1900,1925]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 18. D" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[306,1315,266,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 18. D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 15. Male, dorsal view; 16. Female, dorsal habitus; 17 a. Female, face details (in INHS); 17 b. Female, face details (in CZUG); 18. Female, lateral habitus. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268273/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Figs. 15–17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1575,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">
Head, in dorsal view broader than pronotum. Crown short and not produced, anterior and posterior margins parallel (
<figureCitation box="[251,328,1972,1997]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[199,1390,411,1935]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1392,411,1943]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Head of male holotype of Duocrassana longula gen. and sp. nov. 1. Dorsal view; 2. Frontal view; 3. Lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168335/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[342,373,1972,1996]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 18. D" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[306,1315,266,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 18. D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 15. Male, dorsal view; 16. Female, dorsal habitus; 17 a. Female, face details (in INHS); 17 b. Female, face details (in CZUG); 18. Female, lateral habitus. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268273/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">17</figureCitation>
). Transition of crown to face slightly rounded (
<figureCitation box="[905,985,1972,1997]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[199,1390,411,1935]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1392,411,1943]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Head of male holotype of Duocrassana longula gen. and sp. nov. 1. Dorsal view; 2. Frontal view; 3. Lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168335/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[997,1028,1972,1996]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 18. D" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[306,1315,266,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 18. D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 15. Male, dorsal view; 16. Female, dorsal habitus; 17 a. Female, face details (in INHS); 17 b. Female, face details (in CZUG); 18. Female, lateral habitus. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268273/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">18</figureCitation>
). Texture of anterior margin of head shagreen (
<figureCitation box="[265,403,2008,2033]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 18. D" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[306,1315,266,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 18. D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 15. Male, dorsal view; 16. Female, dorsal habitus; 17 a. Female, face details (in INHS); 17 b. Female, face details (in CZUG); 18. Female, lateral habitus. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268273/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Figs. 15–17</figureCitation>
). Face not strongly tumid in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[869,937,2008,2033]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[199,1390,411,1935]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1392,411,1943]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Head of male holotype of Duocrassana longula gen. and sp. nov. 1. Dorsal view; 2. Frontal view; 3. Lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168335/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Antennal bases near lower corners of eyes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">
Antennae length 1.3x width of head. Antennal ledges weakly carinate, black. Ocelli on anterior margin of head, distance to adjacent eye approximately 1.5x ocellar diameter. Face short, broad. Frontoclypeus moderately broad. Lateral frontal sutures extended to ocelli and continue laterally along each ocellus. Clypellus flat, slightly widened apically. Lorum broad, semicircular, width equal to that of clypellus, lower margin extended close to lower genal margin. Gena incised laterally, covering completely the proepisternum. Frontoclypeus and gena with texture shagreen (
<figureCitation box="[266,374,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[199,1390,411,1935]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1392,411,1943]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Head of male holotype of Duocrassana longula gen. and sp. nov. 1. Dorsal view; 2. Frontal view; 3. Lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168335/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Figs. 2–3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
