<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1544]" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">
Pronotum lateral margin carinate and less than ½ basal width of eye, with weak transverse striations, feebly convex; scutellum not protuberant in lateral and dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[840,947,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[199,1390,411,1935]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1392,411,1943]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Head of male holotype of Duocrassana longula gen. and sp. nov. 1. Dorsal view; 2. Frontal view; 3. Lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168335/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Figs. 1, 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1544]" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">
Forewing macropterous, transparent, appendix restricted to anal margin, apex rounded, apical cells subequal in width and evenly widened distally; with three subapical cells subequal in width, inner anteapical cell open basally (crossvein m-cu2 absent); vein R with three branches, branches not strongly recurved; clavus with crossvein between A1 and claval suture, anal veins not strongly curved, A1–A2 crossvein absent (
<figureCitation box="[1168,1249,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 6. D" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[159,1436,231,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,227,1817]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 6. D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 4. Forewing, dorsal view; 5 a. Front femur, frontal view; 5 b. Front tibia, frontal view; 6 a. Hind tibia, dorsal view; 6 b. Hind tarsomeres, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168336/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1264,1295,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 18. D" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[306,1315,266,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 18. D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 15. Male, dorsal view; 16. Female, dorsal habitus; 17 a. Female, face details (in INHS); 17 b. Female, face details (in CZUG); 18. Female, lateral habitus. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268273/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">18</figureCitation>
). Hindwing, with venation complete, developed and translucent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1544]" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">
Front femur with AM1 near mid-height of apex, long; IC thin, relatively long; row AV with short inconspicuous setae; with two spines at dorsal apex (
<figureCitation box="[743,810,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 6. D" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[159,1436,231,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,227,1817]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 6. D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 4. Forewing, dorsal view; 5 a. Front femur, frontal view; 5 b. Front tibia, frontal view; 6 a. Hind tibia, dorsal view; 6 b. Hind tarsomeres, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168336/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
a). Front tibia with dorsal macrosetal formula (AD+PD) 1+4 (
<figureCitation box="[215,286,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 6. D" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[159,1436,231,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,227,1817]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 6. D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 4. Forewing, dorsal view; 5 a. Front femur, frontal view; 5 b. Front tibia, frontal view; 6 a. Hind tibia, dorsal view; 6 b. Hind tarsomeres, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168336/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
b). Hind femur macrosetal formula 2+2+1; tibia rows with setae as follows: AD–19, PD–10 with intercalary setae (21) and AV–15, PV with numerous short, fine setae (
<figureCitation box="[954,1022,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 6. D" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[159,1436,231,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,227,1817]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 6. D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 4. Forewing, dorsal view; 5 a. Front femur, frontal view; 5 b. Front tibia, frontal view; 6 a. Hind tibia, dorsal view; 6 b. Hind tarsomeres, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168336/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
a); first tarsus long with two rows of 10 setae on ventral surface; each tarsus with two dorsal setae at base; tarsomere I with 4 platellae on pecten (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 6. D" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[159,1436,231,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,227,1817]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 6. D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 4. Forewing, dorsal view; 5 a. Front femur, frontal view; 5 b. Front tibia, frontal view; 6 a. Hind tibia, dorsal view; 6 b. Hind tarsomeres, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168336/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1544]" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">
Male abdominal segment X, long, broad, sclerotized laterally and mostly sclerotized dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1248,1315,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,199,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1855]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 14. Male holotype and female paratype genitalia of D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 7. Pygofer and segment X, lateral view; 8. Pygofer and segment X, dorsal view; 9. Style, dorsal view; 10. Connective, dorsal view; 11. Female sternite VII, ventral view; 12. Aedeagus, lateral view; 13. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 14. Subgenital plates and valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168337/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
), with pair of long ventrolateral processes extended into genital capsule (
<figureCitation box="[846,914,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,199,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1855]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 14. Male holotype and female paratype genitalia of D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 7. Pygofer and segment X, lateral view; 8. Pygofer and segment X, dorsal view; 9. Style, dorsal view; 10. Connective, dorsal view; 11. Female sternite VII, ventral view; 12. Aedeagus, lateral view; 13. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 14. Subgenital plates and valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168337/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Pygofer long and broad, tapering to rounded posterior margin, with numerous dorsoapical macrosetae and band of short, stout setae along distal margin, posterior margin without serrations, ventral margin with large process arising near base and curved posterodorsad (
<figureCitation box="[159,234,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,199,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1855]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 14. Male holotype and female paratype genitalia of D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 7. Pygofer and segment X, lateral view; 8. Pygofer and segment X, dorsal view; 9. Style, dorsal view; 10. Connective, dorsal view; 11. Female sternite VII, ventral view; 12. Aedeagus, lateral view; 13. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 14. Subgenital plates and valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168337/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Valve rounded at posterior margin, articulated with pygofer and subgenital plates. Subgenital plate triangular, as long as pygofer, lateral margin evenly tapered, with row of macrosetae with interspersed small setae (
<figureCitation box="[159,247,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,199,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1855]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 14. Male holotype and female paratype genitalia of D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 7. Pygofer and segment X, lateral view; 8. Pygofer and segment X, dorsal view; 9. Style, dorsal view; 10. Connective, dorsal view; 11. Female sternite VII, ventral view; 12. Aedeagus, lateral view; 13. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 14. Subgenital plates and valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168337/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Style broadly bilobed basally, preapical lobe broadly rounded and not strongly produced, apophysis denticular, gently curved, apex pointed (
<figureCitation box="[616,687,871,896]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,199,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1855]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 14. Male holotype and female paratype genitalia of D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 7. Pygofer and segment X, lateral view; 8. Pygofer and segment X, dorsal view; 9. Style, dorsal view; 10. Connective, dorsal view; 11. Female sternite VII, ventral view; 12. Aedeagus, lateral view; 13. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 14. Subgenital plates and valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168337/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Connective shorter than style (half its length), U–shaped, arms bowed laterad and convergent distally (
<figureCitation box="[600,685,908,933]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,199,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1855]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 14. Male holotype and female paratype genitalia of D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 7. Pygofer and segment X, lateral view; 8. Pygofer and segment X, dorsal view; 9. Style, dorsal view; 10. Connective, dorsal view; 11. Female sternite VII, ventral view; 12. Aedeagus, lateral view; 13. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 14. Subgenital plates and valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168337/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus articulated to connective, shaft robust, curved dorsad, symmetrical, apex bifid, without processes, gonopore subapical on posterior surface, gonoduct sclerotized basad of atrium (
<figureCitation box="[239,377,980,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,199,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1855]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 14. Male holotype and female paratype genitalia of D. longula gen. and sp. nov. 7. Pygofer and segment X, lateral view; 8. Pygofer and segment X, dorsal view; 9. Style, dorsal view; 10. Connective, dorsal view; 11. Female sternite VII, ventral view; 12. Aedeagus, lateral view; 13. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 14. Subgenital plates and valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168337/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Figs. 12–13</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1544]" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">
Female pygofer with numerous macrosetae, ~22 on each side (
<figureCitation box="[928,1015,1015,1040]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24. D" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1896,1919]" captionTargetBox="[165,1413,193,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24. D. longula gen. and sp. nov., female genitalia. 19. First valve, lateral view; 20. Detail of sculpture of first valvula; 21. Second valve, lateral view; 22. Teeth from dorsal margin of second valve; 23. Morphology of tooth; 24. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168339/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor protruding well beyond pygofer apex. First valvula (
<figureCitation box="[469,551,1052,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24. D" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1896,1919]" captionTargetBox="[165,1413,193,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24. D. longula gen. and sp. nov., female genitalia. 19. First valve, lateral view; 20. Detail of sculpture of first valvula; 21. Second valve, lateral view; 22. Teeth from dorsal margin of second valve; 23. Morphology of tooth; 24. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168339/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) dorsal sculpture strigate (
<figureCitation box="[850,934,1052,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24. D" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1896,1919]" captionTargetBox="[165,1413,193,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24. D. longula gen. and sp. nov., female genitalia. 19. First valve, lateral view; 20. Detail of sculpture of first valvula; 21. Second valve, lateral view; 22. Teeth from dorsal margin of second valve; 23. Morphology of tooth; 24. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168339/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
), valvula and ramus slightly convex. Second valvula, abruptly broadened medially and tapered apically (
<figureCitation box="[824,908,1087,1112]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24. D" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1896,1919]" captionTargetBox="[165,1413,193,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24. D. longula gen. and sp. nov., female genitalia. 19. First valve, lateral view; 20. Detail of sculpture of first valvula; 21. Second valve, lateral view; 22. Teeth from dorsal margin of second valve; 23. Morphology of tooth; 24. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168339/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
), dorsal teeth small and obtusely serrate (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24. D" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1896,1919]" captionTargetBox="[165,1413,193,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24. D. longula gen. and sp. nov., female genitalia. 19. First valve, lateral view; 20. Detail of sculpture of first valvula; 21. Second valve, lateral view; 22. Teeth from dorsal margin of second valve; 23. Morphology of tooth; 24. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168339/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">Figs. 22–23</figureCitation>
), without dorsal medial tooth.
</paragraph>
